<!DOCTYPE html> <html> <body> <p>In order to have the application fully deployed, the server had to be delivered by HTTPS.<br>The reason behind is that modern browsers do not allow mixed content, which means that if the client is delivered by https (which is usually the case),</p><p>the server can't be called if its http only.</p><p><img src="https://portfolio.drieam.app/api/public/v1/blobs/545ea1b8-b9c6-4fdf-9e1d-cab50ed05fbf/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBNHBUQVE9PSIsImV4cCI6bnVsbCwicHVyIjoiYmxvYl9pZCJ9fQ==--b5aaacb55306f5c4b6a5b9da1df8da26afe06ae9/cloudflare%20dns%20config.png">Thus, an A rule was added by cloudflare for the external ip of the api gateway. Furthermore, an application gateway had to be added, as well as an ingress controller that sits between the open internet and the application. It further specifies to forward all requests correctly to the application.<br><img src="https://portfolio.drieam.app/api/public/v1/blobs/545ea1b8-b9c6-4fdf-9e1d-cab50ed05fbf/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBNDlUQVE9PSIsImV4cCI6bnVsbCwicHVyIjoiYmxvYl9pZCJ9fQ==--5b1db009b61932e8315444bf81442a32b9f84640/Ingress%20Application%20Gateway.png"></p> </body> </html>